edu.columbia.stat.wood.stochasticmemoizerforsequencedata
Class SMParameters

java.lang.Object
  edu.columbia.stat.wood.hpyp.ParametersAbstract
      edu.columbia.stat.wood.stochasticmemoizerforsequencedata.SMParameters

public class SMParameters
extends edu.columbia.stat.wood.hpyp.ParametersAbstract

A container object for the parameters of a sequence memoizer. For depths >= discounts.length, the discount is discounts[discounts.length -1]^(alpha ^ (depth - discounts.length + 1)). Alpha is set such that the marginal discount value for an infinitely deep restaurant, which governs its relationship to restaurants are the discounts.length - 1 depth, is equal to the infiniteDiscount.

Author:
nicholasbartlett
